<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="117" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[98,749,1185,1952]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">
The protologue of 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="L." box="[344,544,1185,1209]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Arum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arisarum">
<emphasis box="[344,513,1185,1209]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Arum arisarum</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="LINNAEUS" firstAuthor="LINNAEUS" page="966" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" refId="ref1650" refString="LINNAEUS, C. (1753). Species Plantarum. Stockholm." type="book" year="1753">LINNAEUS, 1753: 966</bibRefCitation>
) consists of a short morphological diagnosis, taken from 
<bibRefCitation author="LINNAEUS" box="[98,338,1249,1273]" firstAuthor="LINNAEUS" page="435" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" refId="ref1637" refString="LINNAEUS, C. (1738). Hortus Cliffortianus. Amsterdam." type="book" year="1738">LINNAEUS (1738: 435)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="VAN ROYEN" box="[391,627,1249,1273]" firstAuthor="VAN ROYEN" page="7" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" refId="ref1757" refString="VAN ROYEN, A. (1740). Florae Leydensis prodromus, exhibens plantas quae in horto academico Lugduno-Batavo aluntur. Leiden." type="book" year="1740">VAN ROYEN (1740: 7)</bibRefCitation>
, with three synonyms: two are cited from 
<bibRefCitation author="BAUHIN" box="[437,661,1281,1305]" firstAuthor="BAUHIN" page="196" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" refId="ref1421" refString="BAUHIN, C. (1623). Pinax theatri botanici. Basel, Switzerland." type="book" year="1623">BAUHIN (1623: 196)</bibRefCitation>
: 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">
“ 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Arisarum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="latifolium">Arisarum latifolium</taxonomicName>
majus”
</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[365,703,1313,1337]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">
“ 
<taxonomicName box="[380,591,1313,1337]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Arisarum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="latifolium">Arisarum latifolium</taxonomicName>
alterum”,
</emphasis>
and one referred to 
<bibRefCitation author="CLUSIUS" box="[260,416,1345,1369]" firstAuthor="CLUSIUS" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" refId="ref1470" refString="CLUSIUS, C. (1601). Rariorum plantarum Historia, et Appendix ad Historiam plantarum. Vol. 2. Antwepen." type="book" year="1601">CLUSIUS (1601</bibRefCitation>
: LXXIII, 
<figureCitation box="[526,588,1345,1369]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[825,848,1268,1288]" captionTargetBox="[824,1474,279,1250]" captionTargetId="figure-3360@1.[860,1439,305,1223]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. – Lectotype of Arum arisarum L. (CLUSIUS, 1601: tab. LXXIII)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761904" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5761904/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation author="LOBELIUS" firstAuthor="LOBELIUS" page="598" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" refId="ref1663" refString="LOBELIUS, M. (1581). Plantarum seu Stirpium Icones. Antwepen." type="book" year="1581">LOBELIUS (1581: 598)</bibRefCitation>
<emphasis box="[236,481,1377,1401]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">
“ 
<taxonomicName box="[251,466,1377,1401]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Arisarum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="latifolium">Arisarum latifolium</taxonomicName>
”
</emphasis>
, as well as locality indication “Habitat in Mauritaniae, Italiae, Lusitaniae, Hispaniae, Galloprovinciale nemoribus”. The latter two authors provided the illustrations that can be considered original material. In LINN, the specimen no. 1079.10 (image available at http:// linnean-online.org/11408/) includes the annotation 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">
“15 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Arisarum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Arisarum</taxonomicName>
”,
</emphasis>
explicitly referring to the number of the species account of 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="L." box="[126,313,1601,1625]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Arum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arisarum">
<emphasis box="[126,285,1601,1625]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Arum arisarum</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="LINNAEUS" box="[345,575,1601,1625]" firstAuthor="LINNAEUS" page="966" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" refId="ref1650" refString="LINNAEUS, C. (1753). Species Plantarum. Stockholm." type="book" year="1753">LINNAEUS (1753: 966)</bibRefCitation>
. The sheet bears four specimens certainly to be referred to a single gathering.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761904" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5761904" box="[825,1336,1268,1288]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5761904/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" startId="1.[825,848,1268,1288]" targetBox="[824,1474,279,1250]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph blockId="1.[825,1336,1268,1288]" box="[825,1336,1268,1288]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[825,886,1268,1288]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Fig. 1. –</emphasis>
Lectotype of 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="L." box="[990,1123,1268,1288]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Arum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arisarum">Arum arisarum L.</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="CLUSIUS" box="[1134,1237,1268,1288]" firstAuthor="CLUSIUS" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" refId="ref1470" refString="CLUSIUS, C. (1601). Rariorum plantarum Historia, et Appendix ad Historiam plantarum. Vol. 2. Antwepen." type="book" year="1601">CLUSIUS, 1601</bibRefCitation>
: tab. LXXIII).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="1.[98,749,1185,1952]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">
<bibRefCitation author="BOYCE" box="[136,329,1672,1696]" firstAuthor="BOYCE" page="20" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" pagination="14 - 21" refId="ref1437" refString="BOYCE, P. (1990). Friar's cowls and mouse plants: the genus Arisarum. Bot. Mag. (Kew Mag.) 7: 14 - 21." type="journal article" year="1990">BOYCE (1990: 20)</bibRefCitation>
cited Brander’s specimen in LINN (no. 1079.10) as “holotype”, a typification accepted by 
<bibRefCitation author="GALAN, A." firstAuthor="GALAN" journalOrPublisher="Candollea" page="62" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" pagination="61 - 64" part="62" refId="ref1494" refString="GALAN, A. (2007). Typification of Arisarum simorrhinum Durieu (Araceae). Candollea 62: 61 - 64." title="Typification of Arisarum simorrhinum Durieu (Araceae)" type="journal article" year="2007">GALÁN (2007: 62)</bibRefCitation>
, but not indicated by 
<bibRefCitation author="GALAN &amp; CASTROVIEJO" firstAuthor="GALAN" page="305" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" pagination="304 - 308" refId="ref1556" refString="GALAN, A. &amp; S. CASTROVIEJO (2007). Arisarum Mill. In: CASTRO- VIEJO, S. &amp; al. (ed.), Fl. Iber. 19: 304 - 308. Real Jardin Botanico, CSIC, Madrid." type="journal article" year="2007">GALÁN &amp; CASTROVIEJO (2007: 305)</bibRefCitation>
. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="JARVIS" box="[272,478,1768,1792]" firstAuthor="JARVIS" page="318" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" refId="ref1604" refString="JARVIS, C. E. (2007). Order out of Chaos. Linnaean plant names and their types. Linnean Society of London &amp; Natural History Museum, London." type="book" year="2007">JARVIS (2007: 318)</bibRefCitation>
indicates that this designation is incorrect, because this material was not received by Linnaeus until after 1753. This herbarium sheet (no. 1079.10) has been written by Linnaeus 
<emphasis box="[431,526,1864,1888]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">“Algir”.</emphasis>
The manuscript list 
<emphasis box="[98,336,1896,1920]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">“Algerica Branderi”,</emphasis>
was prepared around 1756 by Daniel Solander from Brander’s specimens (
<bibRefCitation author="JARVIS" box="[525,732,1928,1952]" firstAuthor="JARVIS" page="195" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" refId="ref1604" refString="JARVIS, C. E. (2007). Order out of Chaos. Linnaean plant names and their types. Linnean Society of London &amp; Natural History Museum, London." type="book" year="2007">JARVIS, 2007: 195</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[824,1474,1378,1946]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">
At UPS-BURSER, an herbarium sheet exists with original material (sheet X: 143) (
<figureCitation box="[1095,1158,1410,1434]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[113,136,1268,1288]" captionTargetBox="[113,763,276,1247]" captionTargetId="figure-1939@2.[173,705,289,1234]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. – Original material of Arum arisarum L. [s.coll., UPS-BURSER] [© Herbarium UPS. Reproduced with permission]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5761909/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). The sheet bears two leaves and one label: 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">
“ 
<taxonomicName box="[1000,1215,1442,1466]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Arisarum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="latifolium">Arisarum latifolium</taxonomicName>
alterum Baúh. / [illegible] in Hort. / 143”.
</emphasis>
Linnaeus’s citing the polynomial from 
<bibRefCitation author="BAUHIN" box="[824,994,1506,1530]" firstAuthor="BAUHIN" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" refId="ref1421" refString="BAUHIN, C. (1623). Pinax theatri botanici. Basel, Switzerland." type="book" year="1623">BAUHIN (1623)</bibRefCitation>
provides a link to the specimen in UPSBURSER (Herb. Burser X: 143). Joachim Burser’s herbarium was arranged and labelled according to 
<bibRefCitation author="BAUHIN" box="[1302,1474,1570,1594]" firstAuthor="BAUHIN" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" refId="ref1421" refString="BAUHIN, C. (1623). Pinax theatri botanici. Basel, Switzerland." type="book" year="1623">BAUHIN (1623)</bibRefCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[824,1474,1378,1946]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">
<bibRefCitation author="STEARN, W. T." box="[848,983,1602,1626]" editor="LINNAEUS, C" journalOrPublisher="London" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" part="1753" refId="ref1709" refString="STEARN, W. T. (1957). An introduction to the Species Plantarum and cognate botanical works of Carl Linnaeus. In: LINNAEUS, C, Species Plantarum, a facsimile of the first edition, 1753. Vol. 1. London." title="An introduction to the Species Plantarum and cognate botanical works of Carl Linnaeus" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Species Plantarum, a facsimile of the first edition" year="1957">TEARN, 1957</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="JARVIS" box="[1000,1137,1602,1626]" firstAuthor="JARVIS" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" refId="ref1604" refString="JARVIS, C. E. (2007). Order out of Chaos. Linnaean plant names and their types. Linnean Society of London &amp; Natural History Museum, London." type="book" year="2007">JARVIS, 2007</bibRefCitation>
) and was cited in the introduction to 
<bibRefCitation author="LINNAEUS" box="[901,1085,1634,1658]" firstAuthor="LINNAEUS" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" refId="ref1650" refString="LINNAEUS, C. (1753). Species Plantarum. Stockholm." type="book" year="1753">LINNAEUS (1753)</bibRefCitation>
as one of the sources for that work. This herbarium was in Uppsala when it was used by Linnaeus for the interpretation of the names that appear in Bauhin’s work. Therefore, this specimen is undoubtedly original material. However, unfortunately this specimen is very incomplete, and contains only two very different leaves (
<figureCitation box="[1304,1367,1794,1818]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[113,136,1268,1288]" captionTargetBox="[113,763,276,1247]" captionTargetId="figure-1939@2.[173,705,289,1234]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. – Original material of Arum arisarum L. [s.coll., UPS-BURSER] [© Herbarium UPS. Reproduced with permission]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5761909/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), and this could have led Boyce to designate the sheet in LINN (no. 1079.10) as the holotype. We have been unable to trace any further original material in any of the other Linnaean and Linnaean-linked herbaria (see also 
<bibRefCitation author="JARVIS" box="[1198,1390,1922,1946]" firstAuthor="JARVIS" page="318" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" refId="ref1604" refString="JARVIS, C. E. (2007). Order out of Chaos. Linnaean plant names and their types. Linnean Society of London &amp; Natural History Museum, London." type="book" year="2007">JARVIS, 2007: 318</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761906" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5761906" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5761906/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" startId="2.[839,862,1148,1168]" targetBox="[839,1489,607,1133]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[839,1489,1147,1226]" box="[839,1335,1147,1168]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[839,902,1148,1168]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">Fig. 3. –</emphasis>
Epitype of 
<taxonomicName box="[992,1107,1148,1168]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Arum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arisarum">Arum arisarum</taxonomicName>
L. (designated by an arrow).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[839,1489,1147,1226]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">[P. Ferrer &amp; I. Ferrando 014001, VAL] [© Herbarium VAL. Reproduced with permission]</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761909" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5761909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5761909/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" startId="2.[113,136,1268,1288]" targetBox="[113,763,276,1247]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[113,666,1268,1321]" box="[113,476,1268,1288]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,177,1268,1288]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">Fig. 2. –</emphasis>
Original material of 
<taxonomicName box="[342,458,1268,1288]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Arum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arisarum">Arum arisarum</taxonomicName>
L.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[113,666,1268,1321]" box="[113,666,1300,1321]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">[s.coll., UPS-BURSER] [© Herbarium UPS. Reproduced with permission]</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="2.[113,764,1406,1750]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
Therefore, as the herbarium sheet in UPS-BURSER (Herb. Burser X: 143) is very incomplete, we select here as the lectotype the element of the protologue which best matches the traditional and current concept of 
<emphasis box="[433,598,1502,1526]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
<taxonomicName box="[433,591,1502,1526]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Arum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arisarum">Arum arisarum</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Among the elements cited in the protologue, the illustrations by 
<bibRefCitation author="CLUSIUS" box="[607,764,1534,1558]" firstAuthor="CLUSIUS" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" refId="ref1470" refString="CLUSIUS, C. (1601). Rariorum plantarum Historia, et Appendix ad Historiam plantarum. Vol. 2. Antwepen." type="book" year="1601">CLUSIUS (1601)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="LOBELIUS" box="[157,329,1566,1590]" firstAuthor="LOBELIUS" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" refId="ref1663" refString="LOBELIUS, M. (1581). Plantarum seu Stirpium Icones. Antwepen." type="book" year="1581">LOBELIUS (1581)</bibRefCitation>
clearly shows the characters of the leaves, spathe and spadix as indicated by 
<bibRefCitation author="LINNAEUS" box="[476,658,1598,1622]" firstAuthor="LINNAEUS" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" refId="ref1650" refString="LINNAEUS, C. (1753). Species Plantarum. Stockholm." type="book" year="1753">LINNAEUS (1753)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">“acaule, foliis cordato-oblongis, spatha bifida, spadice incurvo”,</emphasis>
and they are therefore suitable for typification of 
<taxonomicName box="[554,685,1662,1686]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Arum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arisarum">
<emphasis box="[554,685,1662,1686]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">A. arisarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These two illustrations are identical, therefore we designated here the Clusius’s illustration as the lectotype (
<figureCitation box="[504,564,1726,1750]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[825,848,1268,1288]" captionTargetBox="[824,1474,279,1250]" captionTargetId="figure-3360@1.[860,1439,305,1223]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. – Lectotype of Arum arisarum L. (CLUSIUS, 1601: tab. LXXIII)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761904" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5761904/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[113,764,1766,1950]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
However, these images do not show an important diagnostic character for distinguishing this species from 
<taxonomicName box="[592,757,1798,1822]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Arisarum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="simorrhinum">
<emphasis box="[592,757,1798,1822]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">A. simorrhinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
